Close #503
doc(readme): add new entry to ChangeLog about HTTP / HTTPS proxy support
test(unit): add test to ensure proxies are handled via the environment

feat(transporter): implement support for HTTP proxies

This commit brings support for user-defined proxy addresses, defined by
the `HTTP_PROXY` or `HTTPS_PROXY` environment variables, or via the
`Config.proxies` dictionnary of the form:

```py
Config.proxies = {
    'http: 'https://127.0.0.1:8080',
    'https: 'https://127.0.0.1:8080',
}
```

This works for both the `Requester` and the `RequesterAsync`.
feat(transporter): implement __str__ and __repr__ functions for Requester

chore(ci): make CircleCI perform the deploy step upon tagged commit on master

This commit adds an extra step to the CircleCI configuration to release
the project to PyPI if and only if the CI is passing on a semver
tagged commit from master and all tests are passing.

In essence, it prevents the releaser to locally configure PyPI and
fetch credentials and let CircleCI perform the `twine upload` on its own.
